Reasoning: The paper deals with approximation algorithms for stochastic variants of two important combinatorial optimization problems, namely the k-center problem and the set cover problem, under probabilistic constraints. These problems are typically studied in the areas of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), game theory (cs.GT), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and robotics (cs.RO).
